The paper focuses on search-based software engineering (SE) problems and proposes a new approach to solve them using fewer evaluations than traditional evolutionary algorithms. Additionally, the proposed approach involves clustering and culling, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
